{"title":"Thibaut Pinot’s 2023 Tour de France bike: Lapierre Xelius SL3","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/thibaut-pinot-lapierre-xelius-tour-de-france","date":1688734341000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/thibaut-pinot-lapierre-xelius-tour-de-france\">Thibaut Pinot’s 2023 Tour de France bike: Lapierre Xelius SL3</a></p>\n\n<p>In another farewell voyage, this will be <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/5-best-thibaut-pinot\" target=\"_blank\">Thibaut Pinot’s last Tour de France</a> and his <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/lapierre-xelius-sl-9-0-review\" target=\"_blank\">Lapierre Xelius SL3</a> does not disappoint. The Frenchman has ridden with Groupama-FDJ in its many forms for the entirety of his professional career and has been aboard Lapierre bikes throughout – Now That’s What I Call Patriotism. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike itself has been treated to an <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/lapierres-xelius-tour-de-france-2023\" target=\"_blank\">AI-generated paintjob, the Symbiosis edition</a>, created by the Obvious group comprised of three French artists. The shapes and symbols are said to represent biomechanics and movement and is available to buy, though you’ll have to source it direct from Europe. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Thibaut Pinot's 2023 Tour de France bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/thibaut-pinot-bike-lapierre-6.jpg 1800w\" /><figcaption>A mighty high stack of spacers by pro peloton standards. </figcaption><figcaption>Matthew Loveridge / Cyclist</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Pinot is shirking the current trend of narrowing bars that we’ve seen across the rest of the peloton, opting for a 41.5mm cockpit atop a chunky stack of spacers. Over on the mechanic side, the Groupama team have put inner tubes to their sole popular purpose these days in the WorldTour, using them to secure loose Di2 cables across the bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep reading for the full specs and in-depth photos. </p>\n\n\n\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Frameset</td><td>Lapierre Xelius SL3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Levers</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace Di2 12-speed</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Brakes</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace 140mm rotors</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Rear derailleur</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Front derailleur</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Crankset</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace 54/40 172.5mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Cassette</td><td>Dura Ace 11-34</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Chain</td><td>Shimano XTR 12-speed chain M-9100</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Wheels</td><td>Dura-Ace R9270 C50</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Tyres</td><td>Continental GP5000 TLR, 28mm </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Cockpit</td><td>Lapierre Racing Bar UD carbon 41.5mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Headset</td><td>Acros integrated</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Seatpost</td><td>Lapierre carbon seatpost</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Saddle</td><td>Prologo Nago Evo</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Pedals</td><td>Dura-Ace R9100</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Accessories</td><td>Elite Leggero carbon bottle cages</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td><strong>Measurements</strong></td><td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Frame size</td><td>Medium</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Rider height</td><td>1.80m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Rider weight</td><td>63kg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Complete bike weight</td><td>7.45kg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Saddle height, BB to saddle (c-t)</td><td>75cm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Tip of saddle to middle of bar</td><td>58.5cm</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-predictions-2023\">Cyclist’s 2023 Tour de France predictions</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/5-best-thibaut-pinot\">Cyclist’s 5 favourite Thibaut Pinot moments</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/lapierre-xelius-sl-9-0-review\">Lapierre 